The paper discusses a method for fitting models with categorical features, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The use of Laplacian regularization is a technique often used in graph-based methods, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of distributed methods and scalability suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The examples given in the paper involve image classification and time series analysis, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.ST (Statistics) sub-categories.
